  "root_text": {
    "iti67:0.1": "Itivuttaka 67 ",
    "iti67:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti67:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti67:0.4": "Moneyyasutta ",
    "iti67:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti67:2.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, moneyyāni. ",
    "iti67:2.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "iti67:2.3": "Kāyamoneyyaṁ, vacīmoneyyaṁ, manomoneyyaṁ—",
    "iti67:2.4": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi moneyyānī”ti. ",
    "iti67:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti67:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti67:3.1": "“Kāyamuniṁ vacīmuniṁ, ",
    "iti67:3.2": "manomunimanāsavaṁ; ",
    "iti67:3.3": "Muniṁ moneyyasampannaṁ, ",
    "iti67:3.4": "āhu ninhātapāpakan”ti. ",
    "iti67:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti67:4.2": "Aṭṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti67:0.1": "So It Was Said 67 ",
    "iti67:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti67:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti67:0.4": "Sagacity ",
    "iti67:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti67:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three kinds of sagacity. ",
    "iti67:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti67:2.3": "Sagacity of body, speech, and mind. ",
    "iti67:2.4": "These are the three kinds of sagacity.” ",
    "iti67:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti67:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti67:3.1": "“A sage in body, a sage in speech, ",
    "iti67:3.2": "a sage undefiled in mind; ",
    "iti67:3.3": "a sage, blessed with sagacity, ",
    "iti67:3.4": "has washed off all bad things, they say.” ",
    "iti67:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti67:3.4": "āhu ninhātapāpakan”ti → āhu niṇhātapāpakanti (pts-vp-pli1); āhu sabbappahāyinanti (an3.122:1 [122. Moneyyasutta]) "
  },
